definition.value: A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyisobutyric acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxybenzoic acid that is isophthalic acid in which the hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by a hydroxy group.
A member of the class of nitrotoluenes that is 4,6-dinitrotoluene bearing an additional hydroxylamino substituent at position 2.
